text: Mohan Sanjibhai Delkar (19 December 1962 â€“ 22 February 2021) was an Indian politician. He was elected seven times as a member of Lok Sabha (parliament) from Dadra and Nagar Haveli from 1989 to 2009 and from 2019 until his death. He was a member of the Bharatiya Janata Party. Delkar was born in Silvassa, Dadra and Nagar Haveli. Delkar died on 22 February 2021 in Mumbai, Maharashtra at the age of 58.
